# Path Traversal Prevention

Source: cursor-security-rules. Never use raw user input to construct file paths.

## Rule: No User Input in File Paths
- Validate filename format (e.g. allow only `[a-zA-Z0-9._-]+`)
- Use pathlib (Python) or path.resolve() + path.join() (Node); then ensure resolved path is within intended directory
- **Check:** `str(file_path.resolve()).startswith(str(base_dir.resolve()))` (Python) or equivalent

## Safe Patterns
- Use allow-list of allowed filenames when possible
- For uploads: generate safe filenames (e.g. UUID + extension); do not trust user-provided filenames
- Block `..` and path separators in input; be aware of encoding bypasses (`%2e%2e%2f`)

## Common Payloads to Block
- `../../../etc/passwd`, `..\..\..\windows\...`, `....//....//etc/passwd`, URL-encoded variants
